CHAT.comment: Freeplay. Mother and Child sitting on floor with box of experimenter provided toys. First they play with puppet , then truck with shapes. Child is somewhat intelligible.

u.a: waves puppet at Mother so forcefully that it comes of Child's hand .
turns to toy box after puppet comes off .
puts on puppet; waves at Mother .
starts to put away puppets in bag .
picks up and tries one of the shapes .
plays for a few seconds , then says; unclear what Child is intending .
retrieves and starts to place in hole again .
places shape in hole but doesn't let it drop .
tries to push through , looses placement of shape .
